## Steps to Reproduce

1. Create a `TextFormField` with a `onFieldSubmitted` and `textInputAction: TextInputAction.next`
2. Wrap the textField inside a `GestureDetector` which calls `requestFocus(FocusNode())` on a `panDowEvent`
3. Now if you tap the field, type something and press *next* on the keyboard, `onFieldSubmitted` is called
4. If you then swipe the page and try to focus on the text field again and press *next* on the keyboard, `onFieldSubmitted` is not called again

**Expected results:** <!-- what did you want to see? -->

I would expect `onFieldSubmitted` to always be called.

**Actual results:** <!-- what did you see? -->

`onFieldSubmitted` is not called after `requestFocus` on gesture event. Note this only seem to happen on `textInputAction: TextInputAction.next`.

### Example

```
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  // This widget is the root of your application.
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'onSubmitted test',
      home: Page1(),
    );
  }
}

class Page1 extends StatefulWidget {
  @override
  _Page1State createState() => _Page1State();
}

class _Page1State extends State<Page1> {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text('Page 1'),
      ),
      body: GestureDetector(
        behavior: HitTestBehavior.opaque,
        onPanDown: (_) {
          FocusScope.of(context).requestFocus(FocusNode());
        },
        child: Center(
          child: ListTile(
            title: TextFormField(
              onFieldSubmitted: (text) {
                debugPrint('onFieldSubmitted');
              },
              textInputAction: TextInputAction.next,
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

Notice how *onFieldSubmitted* is not printed after you swipe the page.

