@TahaTesser Thank you for re-applying the original labels and titles. I understand and agree with your first two paragraphs, yet again you keep saying `this will surely require updating your code`, as previously simply suggesting the use of a `Stack` widget without even trying it. With all due respect, re-describing the problem without providing any concrete alternative won't help, as I'm suggesting that what I want is actually not possible. Precisely due to the reason you're indicating; I'm pushing a screen within the scope of the `CupertinoTabScaffold`, which basically is the same as if I would place the `Container` with the background image as child of the `CupertinoTabScaffold` (leading to the same result). 

As it actually seems to be impossible to apply a background image that does not resize on normally pushed screens with the device's keyboard; maybe we should propose a feature request..? Like a `backgroundImage` property set on the `CupertinoTabScaffold` widget, which is applied outside of its scope for both the base screen and also for pushed screens, preventing this issue?

For now, I guess the only solution is to stick to `rootNavigator: true`, although that's not really according to the [iOS best tab bar navigation practices](https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/tab-bars#Best-practices).

